HEADWORD: Macrochires
<hw>Mac`ro*chi"res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>makro`s</grk> long + <?/ hand.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of birds including the swifts and humming birds. So
called from the length of the distal part of the wing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

